  "prompt": "What is the scope of civil engineering in California?",
  "response": "California offers extensive opportunities for civil engineers due to several key factors:\n\n1. Infrastructure Development\n- Large-scale transportation projects\n- Highway and bridge construction\n- High-speed rail development\n- Seismic retrofit projects\n\n2. Urban Growth\n- Ongoing urban infrastructure expansion\n- Housing and commercial construction\n- Sustainable development initiatives\n- Smart city infrastructure projects\n\n3. Environmental Engineering\n- Water management systems\n- Drought mitigation projects\n- Flood control infrastructure\n- Climate change adaptation engineering\n\n4. Technological Innovation\n- Advanced infrastructure design\n- Green technology integration\n- Earthquake-resistant structures\n- Sustainable engineering solutions\n\n5. Key Employment Sectors\n- State and local government agencies\n- Private engineering firms\n- Construction companies\n- Transportation departments\n- Environmental consulting firms\n\n6. Specialized Areas\n- Renewable energy infrastructure\n- Coastal engineering\n- Geotechnical engineering\n- Transportation engineering\n\n7. Salary Potential\n- Competitive salaries\n- Average annual wage: $90,000-$120,000\n- Higher earnings in metropolitan areas like San Francisco and Los Angeles\n\n8. Future Prospects\n- Continued infrastructure investment\n- Growing emphasis on sustainability\n- Increasing technological integration\n- Expanding job market\n\nCalifornia provides numerous opportunities for civil engineers across diverse and dynamic sectors.",
